Pre-Game Insights: Jamaica has made two changes to the Reggae Boyz starting team that will play Honduras in Tuesday’s Concacaf Nations League A Group B game at the Nacional Chelato Ucles in Tegucigalpa.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Reggae Boyz were held 0-0 by Cuba in Friday’s opening game played in Kingston and are fourth in the standings going into the game.
Others: Honduras, who beat Trinidad and Tobago 4-0 in their first game, which was also played at home are second on the points table that are being led by Nicaragua who have four points from their two games played.
